author: dandiep
msg: o Get Wrapped interceptors working with other interceptors. This involved
mostly having them use Exchange properties instead of Message properties
and throwing Faults corectly. Also, I created a flag on operations which
signals that it can be unwrapped into separate parts. If it can, it does
so using WrapperHelper. WrapperHelper still needs to figure out the
class involved, so it can do its Boolean magic, but wanted to keep
moving towards helloworld...
o More flagrant ugly use of ExchangeConstants for now as many constants
on Message were Exchange constants.
o Used message.getContent(Object.class) instead of the invocation objects
property and the properties on ServiceInvokerInterceptor.
o Commented out RPC interceptors for now as it will take a bit more work to get
them and their tests up to speed with the Wrapped/Bare stuff. I am trying to
focus on the HelloWorld stuff instead. If someone thinks I should revisit
this immediately let me know (or someone else could too). I think they could
relatively easily extend the WrappedInterceptors which should make those
classes very simple. The only thing that should need to change between them
is the outgoing namespace on the RPCOutInterceptor.
